<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,279,629]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,388,413]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species could be distinguished from its congeners by: 1) antennae dark brown, basal three antennomeres with both reddish apex and bases; 2) antennomere II longer than III; 3) anterior 2/3 of dorsal surface of head bearing dense small punctures, also on frontal region; 4) admedian row of pronotum consisting of 8–9 punctures; lateral row, curvedly arranged, of 8–9 punctures; 5) mesoscutellum bearing transverse microstriae; 6) interspaces between punctures on abdomen ca. 3–4 punctures’ diameter; 7) surface between two basal transverse carinae of each tergite impunctate, but bearing distinct transverse microstriae; 8) inner sac dark color, tape-like, coiled 3 or 4 times, without large spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
